.TH UNAME "1" "April 2026" "GNU coreutils 9.11" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
uname \- print system information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B uname
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" Add any additional description here
.PP
Print certain system information.  With no OPTION, same as \fB\-s\fR.
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#uname-a'\fB\-a, \-\-all\fP\X'tty: link'
print all information, in the following order,
except omit \fB\-p\fR and \fB\-i\fR if unknown
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#uname-s'\fB\-s, \-\-kernel\-name\fP\X'tty: link'
print the kernel name
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#uname-n'\fB\-n, \-\-nodename\fP\X'tty: link'
print the network node hostname
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#uname-r'\fB\-r, \-\-kernel\-release\fP\X'tty: link'
print the kernel release
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#uname-v'\fB\-v, \-\-kernel\-version\fP\X'tty: link'
print the kernel version
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#uname-m'\fB\-m, \-\-machine\fP\X'tty: link'
print the machine hardware name
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#uname-p'\fB\-p, \-\-processor\fP\X'tty: link'
print the processor type (non\-portable)
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#uname-i'\fB\-i, \-\-hardware\-platform\fP\X'tty: link'
print the hardware platform (non\-portable)
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#uname-o'\fB\-o, \-\-operating\-system\fP\X'tty: link'
print the operating system
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/uname#uname--help'\fB\-\-help\fP\X'tty: link'
display this help and exit
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/uname#uname--version'\fB\-\-version\fP\X'tty: link'
output version information and exit
